cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using tactile sensors for robot manipulation tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end learning strategy using deep reinforcement learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the GelSight sensor is a type of vision-based tactile sensor. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a learning-based approach for surface following. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper deals with controlling the motion of a robot end-effector based on tactile feedback.
